Season summary: 4545 League, Season 13

Overview

  • The season ran from 2 Jul 2018 to 26 Aug 2018.
  • 209 players took part, playing 481 games in total. 74 games were either forfeited or set as scheduling draws.
  • Across the season, White won 209 games (43.5%), 91 games (18.9%) were drawn, and Black won 181 games (37.6%).
  • 302 games ended with a resignation, 77 games by checkmate, 11 games by time running out, and 6 games by stalemate.

Best relative perfs

Shows all players who achieved a performance rating (over a minimum of 5 games) that exceeded their initial rating.

For what its worth, I use FIDEs method (which the website does too), and I ignore all unplayed games such as forfeits and scheduling draws.

Draws, comebacks, upsets

Most draws

Comebacks

Originally suggested by Lou-E.

This table shows players ranked by the size and number of comebacks achieved over the course of the season.

For this purpose, the size of a comeback has been defined as the difference between a players final score in a game (0, 0.5, or 1) and the worst evaluation during the game that they faced (which is then converted into a rough win probability for their opponent).

For example, if I were to win a game after Lichesss server analysis gave my opponent a 75% chance of winning in a certain position, then I would have earned 1.75 comeback points from the game. My opponent of course would have earned zero points. If the game had been drawn, I would have instead earned only 0.75 comeback points.

Only those who played at least three games in the season and who have a positive average comeback margin are included.

Misc. facts

Lesser spotted mates

A pawn gave checkmate in 3 games: https://lichess.org/HYpdDD5K, https://lichess.org/xNafqKW0, https://lichess.org/vXLhsjG2.

A knight gave checkmate in 6 games: https://lichess.org/RbeDVNpd, https://lichess.org/FqNP8vZr, https://lichess.org/gSUpEYrL, https://lichess.org/YjpMYTwA, https://lichess.org/KRc14q8X, https://lichess.org/1Ph2gXwK.

Promotions

48 games had at least one promotion. 1 of these saw an under-promotion.

The most promotions seen in a game was 3: https://lichess.org/ocGfQQUJ, https://lichess.org/vVugxqSY

Rollercoaster games

26 games featured significant winning chances for both sides (as identified by Lichesss server analysis), comprising 5.4% of all games played.

  • Most consecutive checks: 9 (https://lichess.org/AstwS67b, https://lichess.org/lKNBFsvi)

About

  • This report was compiled on 30 July 2021.
  • It uses data on player/team pairings and results from the Lichess4545 website combined with game data provided by Lichess.
  • Note that the data excludes all players who are currently banned by Lichess for violating their Terms of Service (at the time the report was compiled). This can mean that players who are listed in the final standings on the Lichess4545 website are missing from the statistics presented here.
  • Although tournament performance ratings have been calculated using FIDEs method, they may differ slightly from figures published on the Lichess4545 website.
  • Currently, ties are not properly handled when determining player awards, which may cause errors.
  • Also, the code that produces the stats does not implement tiebreaks to determine the top three 4545 teams. This usually works out fine, but it can lead to errors in seasons where the top positions were determined by tiebreaks most notably in Season 11.
  • Icons for player awards: Noun Project

Stats produced by izzie26
